  "prompt": "Can I use digital locker facility to sign my documents using Aadhar verification and use it in place of e-mudhra digital signature?",
  "response": "Digital Lockers (DigiLocker) and Digital Signatures (e-Mudhra) serve different purposes, but both can be used for document authentication and verification:\n\nDigiLocker:\n- Government-issued digital document storage platform\n- Provides document authentication using Aadhaar\n- Can store and share government-issued documents\n- Limited digital signature capabilities\n\ne-Mudhra Digital Signature:\n- Legally recognized digital signature certificate\n- Provides comprehensive digital signing capabilities\n- Used for legally binding electronic signatures\n- Issued by Certifying Authorities (CAs)\n\nKey Differences:\n1. Legal validity: e-Mudhra has full legal recognition for all document signing\n2. Scope: DigiLocker is primarily for document storage and verification\n3. Usage: e-Mudhra is more widely accepted for official and legal document signing\n\nRecommendations:\n- For official/legal documents: Use e-Mudhra digital signature\n- For document storage and basic verification: Use DigiLocker\n- For comprehensive digital signing needs: Obtain an e-Mudhra certificate\n\nWhile DigiLocker can authenticate documents using Aadhaar, it cannot completely replace e-Mudhra for all digital signature requirements.",
